Package: voiageR
Type: Package
Title: Value of Information Analysis in R
Version: 0.2.1
Author: voiage Development Team
Maintainer: voiage Development Team <voiage@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: An R interface to the Rust-backed voiage core for Value of Information analysis,
    with a direct Rust C ABI EVPI path and helper functions for Python environment management
    where advanced methods still use reticulate. Provides functions for calculating Expected Value of Perfect Information
    (EVPI), Expected Value of Partial Perfect Information (EVPPI), and Expected Value of
    Sample Information (EVSI).
URL: https://github.com/edithatogo/voiage
BugReports: https://github.com/edithatogo/voiage/issues
License: Apache License (>= 2.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
NeedsCompilation: no
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Config/testthat/edition: 3
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.12)
Suggests:
    reticulate (>= 1.20),
    knitr (>= 1.45),
    rmarkdown (>= 2.26),
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
